Integument with longish, slightly curved main papillae surrounded by six flat elevations (
<figureCitation box="[1329,1432,1125,1151]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1935,1960]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,234,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[151,1436,229,1915]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 11. Family Hydrodromidae, genus Hydrodroma. a.–d. H. lasioderma female (MD 120a); a. integument structure; b. III-L-5–6; c. IV-L-5–6; d. Cx-I+II; e.–h. H. mesembrina male (MD 151); e. coxal and genital field; f. integument papillae; g. III-L-4–6; h. IV-L-4–6." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613324/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Figs 11 f</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,223,1161,1188]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1330,1355]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,174,1310]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,174,1310]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 12. Family Hydrodromidae, genus Hydrodroma. a.–e. H. lasioderma (MD 154b); a.–b. female and male Cx-I+II; c.–e. integument papillae in various views; f.–i. H. mesembrina (MD 151); f. female Cx-I+II; g.–i. integument papillae in various views; k.–n. H. zhokhovi female; k. Cx-I+II; l.–n. integument papillae in various views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613326" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613326/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<quantity box="[151,200,1161,1187]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.2" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="g" value="12.0">12 g</quantity>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[200,214,1161,1187]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">–</emphasis>
i
</figureCitation>
). Lateral eyes lens diameter anterior 35 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[666,680,1161,1187]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">–</emphasis>
65, posterior 25 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[856,870,1161,1187]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">–</emphasis>
55, distance 20 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1038,1052,1161,1187]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">–</emphasis>
55. Medial margin Cx-I smooth or with very inconspicuous projections near setae bases; tips with 5 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[873,887,1197,1223]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">–</emphasis>
7 strong setae (
<figureCitation box="[1055,1160,1197,1223]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1935,1960]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,234,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[151,1436,229,1915]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 11. Family Hydrodromidae, genus Hydrodroma. a.–d. H. lasioderma female (MD 120a); a. integument structure; b. III-L-5–6; c. IV-L-5–6; d. Cx-I+II; e.–h. H. mesembrina male (MD 151); e. coxal and genital field; f. integument papillae; g. III-L-4–6; h. IV-L-4–6." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613324/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Figs 11 e</figureCitation>
